org.eclipse.incquery.runtime.matchers.context

Interface IQueryRuntimeContext

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DynamicEMFQueryRuntimeContext, EMFQueryRuntimeContext

    public interface IQueryRuntimeContext
    Provides instance model information (relations corresponding to input keys) to query evaluator backends at runtime.
    Author:
    Bergmann Gabor

      • coalesceTraversals

        <V> V coalesceTraversals(java.util.concurrent.Callable<V> callable)
                  throws java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException
        The given callable will be executed, and all model traversals will be delayed until the execution is done. If there are any outstanding information to be read from the model, a single coalesced model traversal will initialize the caches and deliver the notifications.

        Calls may be nested. A single coalesced traversal will happen at the end of the outermost call.

        Caution: results returned by the runtime context may be incomplete during the coalescing period, to be corrected by notifications sent during the final coalesced traversal. For example, if a certain input key is not cached yet, an empty relation may be reported during callable.call(); the cache will be constructed after the call terminates and notifications will deliver the entire content of the relation. Non-incremental query backends should therefore never enumerate input keys while coalesced (verify using isCoalescing()).

        Parameters:
        callable -
        Throws:
        java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException

      • isCoalescing

        boolean isCoalescing()
        Returns:
        true iff currently within a coalescing section (i.e. within the callable of a call to coalesceTraversals(Callable)).

      • isIndexed

        boolean isIndexed(IInputKey key)
        Returns:
        true iff the given input key is already indexed, and contents are available without costly model traversal.

      • ensureIndexed

        void ensureIndexed(IInputKey key)
        If the given (enumerable) input key is not yet indexed, the model will be traversed (after the end of the outermost coalescing block, see coalesceTraversals(Callable)) so that the index can be built.

        Postcondition: After invoking this method, isIndexed(IInputKey) for the same key will be guaranteed to return true as soon as isCoalescing() first returns false.

        Precondition: the given key is enumerable, see IQueryMetaContext.isEnumerable(IInputKey).

        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if key is not enumerable, see IQueryMetaContext.isEnumerable(IInputKey).

      • countTuples

        int countTuples(IInputKey key,
                Tuple seed)
        Returns the number of tuples in the extensional relation identified by the input key, optionally seeded with the given tuple.
        Parameters:
        key - an input key
        seed - can be null or a tuple with matching arity; if non-null, only those tuples in the model are counted that match the seed at positions where the seed is non-null.
        Returns:
        the number of tuples in the model for the given key and seed

        Precondition: the given key is enumerable, see IQueryMetaContext.isEnumerable(IInputKey).

      • enumerateValues

        java.lang.Iterable<? extends java.lang.Object> enumerateValues(IInputKey key,
                                                               Tuple seed)
        Simpler form of enumerateTuples(IInputKey, Tuple) in the case where all values of the tuples are bound by the seed except for one.

        Selects the tuples in the extensional relation identified by the input key, optionally seeded with the given tuple, and then returns the single value from each tuple which corresponds to the only null value in the seed.

        Parameters:
        key - an input key
        seed - can be null (if key is unary) or a tuple with matching arity; if non-null, only those tuples in the model are enumerated that match the seed at positions where the seed is non-null; the seed is null at exactly one position.
        Returns:
        the objects in the model for the given key and seed

        Precondition: the given key is enumerable, see IQueryMetaContext.isEnumerable(IInputKey).

        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if key is not enumerable, see IQueryMetaContext.isEnumerable(IInputKey).

      • containsTuple

        boolean containsTuple(IInputKey key,
                      Tuple seed)
        Simpler form of enumerateTuples(IInputKey, Tuple) in the case where all values of the tuples are bound by the seed.

        Returns whether the given tuple is in the extensional relation identified by the input key.

        Note: this call works for non-enumerable input keys as well.

        Parameters:
        key - an input key
        seed - a tuple with matching arity, consisting of non-null elements (null can be used in the 0-ary case).
        Returns:
        true iff the seed tuple is contained in the relation
